messages.content:
=Create a post-mortem document template for this resolved incident.

Incident:
- ID: {{ $('On PagerDuty Incident').item.json.body.event.data.id }}
- Title: {{ $('On PagerDuty Incident').item.json.body.event.data.title }}
- Service: {{ $json.result.message.parseJson().service_name }}
- Duration: {{ $json.result.message.parseJson().incident_duration_minutes }} minutes
- Created: {{ $('On PagerDuty Incident').item.json.body.event.data.created_at }}
- Resolved: {{ $('On PagerDuty Incident').item.json.body.event.data.resolved_at }}

Context:
{{ $json.result.message }}

Create a structured post-mortem template as JSON:
{
  "title": "Post-Mortem: [incident title]",
  "summary": "Brief 2-3 sentence summary",
  "timeline": [
    {"time": "HH:MM", "event": "Incident detected"},
    {"time": "HH:MM", "event": "Response initiated"},
    {"time": "HH:MM", "event": "Root cause identified"},
    {"time": "HH:MM", "event": "Resolution applied"},
    {"time": "HH:MM", "event": "Incident resolved"}
  ],
  "impact": "Description of customer/business impact",
  "root_cause_analysis": "[To be filled during post-mortem meeting]",
  "action_items": [
    {"action": "Suggested action 1", "owner": "TBD", "due_date": "TBD"},
    {"action": "Suggested action 2", "owner": "TBD", "due_date": "TBD"}
  ],
  "lessons_learned": "[To be filled during post-mortem meeting]",
  "meeting_attendees": []
}

Return ONLY the JSON object.

parameters.prompt:
=An incident has been resolved and needs a post-mortem meeting scheduled.

Incident Details:
- ID: {{ $('On PagerDuty Incident').item.json.body.event.data.id }}
- Title: {{ $('On PagerDuty Incident').item.json.body.event.data.title }}
- Service: {{ $('Parse Context (Resolved)').item.json.result.message.parseJson().service_name }}
- Duration: {{ $('Parse Context (Resolved)').item.json.result.message.parseJson().incident_duration_minutes }} minutes
- Resolved At: {{ $('On PagerDuty Incident').item.json.body.event.data.resolved_at }}

Stakeholders to invite:
{{ $('Parse Context (Resolved)').item.json.result.message.parseJson().stakeholders_to_invite.join(', ') || $('Parse Context (Resolved)').item.json.result.message.parseJson().owners.join(', ') }}

Post-Mortem Template:
{{ $('Generate Post-Mortem Template').item.json.message.content }}

Your tasks:
1. Create a post-mortem document (in Confluence/Notion if available) with the template content
2. Schedule a post-mortem meeting for 2-3 business days from now
3. Invite relevant stakeholders (service owners, on-call engineers who responded)
4. Include the incident details and post-mortem document link in the meeting invite

Respond with JSON:
{
  "document_created": true or false,
  "document_url": "URL if created",
  "meeting_scheduled": true or false,
  "meeting_time": "ISO timestamp",
  "attendees_invited": [],
  "status": "success|partial|failed",
  "message": "Summary of actions taken"
}

